James de Villiers, News24 (Joe Stolley, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories George &ndash; A baby drowned in a bucket of water in an informal settlement in Wilderness, George, on Thursday, emergency services said.&nbsp;When emergency services arrived on scene the baby was found dead, NSRI Wilderness station commander Robert van Helsdingen said in a statement.Helsdingen said the baby is believed to have drowned accidentally.The age of the baby is unknown at this stage.&nbsp;The body of the baby was taken to Police and the Forensic Pathology Services.An inquest docket has been opened.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.